27/04/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A meeting of the foreign ministers of the Black Sea Economic Co-operation (BSEC) initiative on Wednesday (26 April) marked the end of Romania's six-month term as BSEC chairman.
Russia assumes the rotating post as of 1 May.
Meeting participants discussed specific projects aimed at developing the transport, energy, telecommunications, trade and customs sectors.
They also confirmed their commitment to strengthening regional security and stability through fighting trans-border crime, human trafficking and terrorism.
(Nine o'clock - 27/04/06;
Rompres, BNR, ANA - 26/04/06)
